reviews.text: One of the few truly old-fashioned traditional sandstone parish churches in Canberra. But not original, it was the Rookwood Cemetery Station from Sydney and imported stone by stone to Ainslie. The mods were sympathetic and so is a delight to visit even if you are not religiously inclined.
They are always very very Helpful there and just a great bunch of people
Very beautiful place, definitely worth it to be seen in Canberra!
Fantastic stain glassed window behind the altar of the church.
One of the oldest church in Canberra.
